race.comment: Tough way to finish the program but hopefully the punters are well up by this stage of the afternoon. At a price, happy to have something on AVANZO (16) who has built a decent record since joining the Rutten stable. She's shown glimpses of her best in three runs this preparation and might be ready to peak. The wide draw is a concern but she can run well in an open race. BROOKLYN BABY (10) is a newcomer to SA and can make an immediate impact here. She's got no weight after the claim so will roll forward and give a sight. DE LUCA (8) can improve sharply and is another worth some thought on an each-way basis. She draws well and maps to get the favours. WHOOPS A DAISY (15) has ability but her winning strike rate makes her hard to back with confidence. Include as a place chance. COSTLESS (5) is another that might be able to sneak into the money at his first run for the new stable.
